From 5081fe8178738480e142f21d1b47d0fbee17026a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: picoclaw-ci <ci@picoclaw.dev>
Date: Tue, 17 Mar 2026 19:13:52 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] docs: add quick install one-liner for custom fork

Add a prominent install block at the top of the README with a single
command to clone, apply patches, and build the custom fork. Lists
the active patches and links to PATCHES.md for details.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 README.md | 10 ++++++++++
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+)

diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
index 159ac70..0c6c612 100644
--- a/README.md
+++ b/README.md
@@ -24,6 +24,16 @@
 
 ---
 
+> **Quick Install (Custom Fork by [@paoloanzn](https://github.com/paoloanzn/picoclaw))**
+>
+> ```bash
+> git clone https://github.com/paoloanzn/picoclaw && cd picoclaw && ./scripts/apply-patches.sh && cd vendor/picoclaw && make install
+> ```
+>
+> Includes: SOP framework, relaxed exec guard, subagent tool fix. See [PATCHES.md](https://github.com/paoloanzn/picoclaw/blob/main/PATCHES.md) for details.
+
+---
+
 🦐 PicoClaw is an ultra-lightweight personal AI Assistant inspired by [nanobot](https://github.com/HKUDS/nanobot), refactored from the ground up in Go through a self-bootstrapping process, where the AI agent itself drove the entire architectural migration and code optimization.
 
 ⚡️ Runs on $10 hardware with <10MB RAM: That's 99% less memory than OpenClaw and 98% cheaper than a Mac mini!
